<Base title="Affordable Baremetrics Alternatives for Early-Stage SaaS (2026)" description="Baremetrics is great but expensive for indie founders. Here are the best affordable alternatives for tracking SaaS metrics like MRR, Churn, and LTV.">
  <article class="blog-post">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="post-header">
        <time datetime="2026-04-07">April 7, 2026</time>
        <h1>Affordable Baremetrics Alternatives for Early-Stage SaaS (2026)</h1>
        <p class="post-lead">
          When you're making $500/mo, spending $108/year on analytics feels like a bad joke. Let's look at what else is out there.
        </p>
      </header>

      <div class="post-body">
        <p>
          Don't get me wrong — Baremetrics is a solid product. If you're doing $10K+ MRR with a team, it's probably worth it. But if you're a solo founder in the early days, their pricing can feel like a kick in the teeth.
        </p>
        <p>
          I went through this myself. I wanted a simple dashboard to see my MRR and churn rate, and every tool I found either cost too much or wanted me to install a 50-step data pipeline. So I started looking for alternatives, and eventually built one myself.
        </p>
        <p>
          Here's what I found.
        </p>

        <h2>What we're comparing</h2>
        <p>
          For this comparison, I'm focused on what early-stage indie SaaS founders actually need:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Stripe integration (most of us use Stripe)</li>
          <li>Core metrics: MRR, ARR, Churn Rate, LTV, ARPU</li>
          <li>Revenue breakdown (new, expansion, contraction, churned)</li>
          <li>Affordable pricing (ideally under $30/mo)</li>
          <li>Quick setup (under 5 minutes, ideally)</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>1. Baremetrics</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>Price:</strong> Starts at $108/year (Starter plan). Goes up from there based on MRR.<br />
          <strong>Pros:</strong> Comprehensive metrics, beautiful UI, forecasting features, multiple payment processor support.<br />
          <strong>Cons:</strong> Expensive for early-stage founders. The free trial is only 14 days. Some features are locked behind higher tiers.
        </p>
        <p>
          Baremetrics is the default recommendation you'll see everywhere, and for good reason. It's polished and feature-complete. But the cost doesn't make sense when your MRR is under a few thousand dollars.
        </p>

        <h2>2. ChartMogul</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>Price:</strong> Free up to $10K MRR. Paid plans start at $100/mo.<br />
          <strong>Pros:</strong> Free tier is generous. Good segmentation features. Supports multiple data sources.<br />
          <strong>Cons:</strong> The free tier lacks some analytics features. Paid plans jump to $100/mo quickly. Can be complex to set up.
        </p>
        <p>
          ChartMogul's free tier is genuinely useful if you're under $10K MRR. The catch is that once you outgrow it, the jump to paid is steep. Still, if you want a mature tool and you're under that threshold, it's worth a look.
        </p>

        <h2>3. ProfitWell (by Paddle)</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>Price:</strong> Free for core metrics.<br />
          <strong>Pros:</strong> Free! Good retention analysis. Solid benchmarking data.<br />
          <strong>Cons:</strong> Now owned by Paddle, so the Stripe integration has become less of a priority. Setup can be clunky. The upsell to paid retention features is aggressive.
        </p>
        <p>
          ProfitWell used to be the go-to free option. Since the Paddle acquisition, the experience for Stripe users has gotten a bit worse. Still free though, which counts for a lot.
        </p>

        <h2>4. Stripe Dashboard + spreadsheets</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>Price:</strong> Free (with your time).<br />
          <strong>Pros:</strong> No additional tool. You control everything.<br />
          <strong>Cons:</strong> Stripe doesn't natively calculate MRR, churn, or LTV. You'll spend hours building and maintaining formulas. Gets out of date the moment you stop updating it.
        </p>
        <p>
          This is where most indie founders start. And honestly? For your first 10 customers, a spreadsheet is fine. But the moment you need to make a real decision based on trends, it falls apart.
        </p>

        <h2>5. MRRScope</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>Price:</strong> Free demo mode. $29 one-time (or $9.99/mo) for real Stripe data.<br />
          <strong>Pros:</strong> Built specifically for indie founders. All 6 core metrics. Ridiculously fast setup. One-time pricing option. Demo mode lets you try before buying.<br />
          <strong>Cons:</strong> Stripe only (no Paddle yet). Fewer features than enterprise tools. Newer product.
        </p>
        <p>
          Full disclosure: I built <a href="/fixitdev-site/tools/mrrscope">MRRScope</a>. So take this with a grain of salt. But the reason I built it is exactly this comparison — I went through every option above and none of them hit the sweet spot of "affordable, simple, and actually shows me my MRR in under 2 minutes."
        </p>
        <p>
          MRRScope connects to Stripe with one click, calculates MRR, ARR, Churn, LTV, ARPU, and gives you revenue breakdown charts. The free demo mode uses sample data so you can explore everything before committing.
        </p>

        <h2>So which one should you pick?</h2>
        <p>Here's my honest take:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Under $1K MRR and want free:</strong> ChartMogul free tier or ProfitWell.</li>
          <li><strong>Under $5K MRR and want simple:</strong> <a href="/fixitdev-site/tools/mrrscope">MRRScope</a>. $29 one-time, done.</li>
          <li><strong>Over $10K MRR with a team:</strong> Baremetrics or ChartMogul paid. You can afford it and need the advanced features.</li>
          <li><strong>Just starting out:</strong> Try <a href="/fixitdev-site/tools/mrrscope">MRRScope's demo mode</a> to learn what the metrics look like. It's free and requires no sign-up.</li>
        </ul>

        <p>
          The worst option is tracking nothing. Whatever tool you choose, just start looking at your numbers.
        </p>

        <div class="post-cta">
          <h3>Try MRRScope's free demo</h3>
          <p>See all 6 SaaS metrics with sample data. No sign-up, no credit card. Connect Stripe when you're ready.</p>
          <a href="/fixitdev-site/tools/mrrscope" class="cta-btn">Try MRRScope Free</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>

